"n. 神化; 典范 【英】 n.神化(the act of raising a person to the status of a god; deification)；典范(a glorified ideal) 【记】 apo+theo(神)+sis→ 离神不远→神化; 【同】 参考：deify(神化)同根词：theology(神 学); atheism(无神论) n. 神化, 尊为神(使宗教地位升高发展的行为); 典范(尊崇颂扬的典型) 【例】He was the apotheosis of courage 他领导人是勇敢的典范. 【记】1)apo变更, theos神－变更为神－神化2)a一个, pot小瓶子－装着可以满足你三个愿望的神－神话 【参】theology(n 神学); atheism(n 无神论); deify(v 神化) 【记】apo + theo 神 + sis，渐渐远离，上昇，成仙 apotheosis (n.)  1600s, from Late Latin apotheosis ""deification,"" from Greek apotheosis, from apotheoun ""deify, make (someone) a god,"" from apo- special use of this prefix, meaning, here, ""change"" + theos ""god"" (see theo-)."
